annotationA: Accessory gland protein 26Aa (Acp26Aa) is synthesized in male accessory glands. It is transferred during mating to females where it induces an increase in ovulation by relaxing the oviduct via activation of octopaminergic signaling
annotationB: Accessory gland protein 53C14a, isoform A; It is involved in the biological process described with: multicellular organism reproduction
